description: Deeper into the dark forest you go.  The animals around you, stop
for a moment to make sure you are not dangerous, and the forest seems
to go quiet.  Then as quickly as the silence comes, the noise starts
back up again.  With each step, the animals do this little game...
19479.name: The Industrial Road

description: The western catwalk runs along the western side of the massive
building.  You see large port hatches lined up with gates along the
side of the catwalk.
19511.name: {MW{mestern{x {MC{matwalk{x

description: The wind makes the grass move with an unearthly unison here, like smooth
waves in thick liquid.  The sound seems to be a loud hissing sound, like
many thousands of angry snakes.  This throws into contrast the gentle sound
of running water some distance to the north.
19412.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: The road north is dusty and humid from past rains, the slight muddyness
of the road creates a dismal air to the road, which is pinned between the
Istar Coast and the Mirkwood Forest.  The slight chirping of crickets stops
abruptly as you proceed by, and with that, the terrain becomes deathly
quiet.  Even the coasts itself, seem to make no noise as you walk the path
to the Country of Vector.
19401.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: You can see the capitol fortress of vector in the distance, as well as
the City of St.  Plattsburg.  A calm, humid wind blows from the sea of
Istar, keeping a dampness to everything in sight.  The sky to the north
looks clouded with brown smoke, from the industries of Vector.
19446.name: The Road To St.Plattsburg

description: This is what could be called the governing power of this hamlet, being
the place where all relevant documents are kept.  Also the largest house in
the town, it probably previously was owned by a rich townsman.  There are a
few paintings on the walls, depicting the village over the decades.
19469.name: The Town Hall

description: {bThe waves of the Istar Sea slowly flow over each other,
{bsmall almost ripples.  The deep blue waters of the sea
{bprotect what lies beneath, the darkness hiding unknown
{bcreatures.  The water is almost surrounding, only the creset
{bof a coastline appears on the hoizon.
19782.name: {BT{bhe {CI{Bs{bt{Ba{Cr {bSe{Ba{x

description: On the outskirts of the town of "{^Lucullus{x", the sounds of life throw
a mirror compared to the empty feelings of the endless road.  The north
holds activity, not pesantry activity like the town, but a more sinister
one.  The borderline of Vector lies northwest.
19419.name: Outskirts of Lucullus

room in the building at the top.
19495.name: {MW{mest {MA{mirship {MT{mower{*: {ML{mevel {R2{x

description: The outter wall of the prison still stands to the west, the gates
still there.  The gates opened up into a field, which was used to
allow the prisoners to run around for a few hours, being watched very
carefully.  Now a dirt road leads south to the Tower Structures and
all the rest of the compound.
19522.name: {MT{mhe {MP{mrison {MN{mo {MM{more{x

description: You approach the border of The Tripower Lands, strangely there are no
Tripower representitve guards patrolling the lands.  A long walk lies ahead
of you, whichever side you wish to go on to.
19423.name: The Road To Vector

description: Hugging the coastline, the road to St.  Plattsburg twists, turns, and
meanders like a snake.  A damn humid feeling lingers in the air, thick
enough to moisten your clothes, and keeps everything in an uncomfortable
warmpth.
19439.name: The Road To St.Plattsburg

description: As you walk along the road traversing the town, a house that looks larger
and stylish compared to the others sits on the west.  Perhaps the Town hall?
Opposite the Town hall, is advertized to be a general store by a sign
hanging above the door.  The people here hustle along with daily life, and
nod in notice to your presence.
19417.name: Center of Lucullus

description: Finely varnished hardwood floors hold your dull reflection as you walk
along the hall.  Local paintings adorn the walls, and a small mat to hold a
small table with a vase.
19459.name: Second floor if the Inn

description: The road, dusty and dry, gives small clouds of dirt to the air as you

the east across the bay.
19424.name: The Road To Vector

description: Deep inside the Mirkwoods, there is a humid mist that seeps along the
ground here, covering the entire floor as far as you can see.  It's too
thick to see through, and seems to hug at your legs, not moving for any
reason.  Hopefully, you won't step on anything too dangerous.

long city street, but no buildings around it.  A large railway to the
northeast leads to the MAGITEK FACTORY, in which espers are processed
and Magitek Armor is built.  To the west is barren land, large stone
slabs dott the area.  The street goes north, the gates of Vector are

19447.name: The Road To St.Plattsburg

description: As you travel along the dirt road, you approach a small hamlet.  A small
village of fishers and hunters.  The smell of cooking meat and drying fish
fill your nostrils.  A very sequestered village, kept alive only with the
travel of caravans every now and again.
19414.name: Approaching Lucullus

description: You can see the fortress in the distance.  It looks almost impenetrable,
with it's solid cemented walls, and many guards.  The Fortress itself also
has blackened areas and heavily damaged areas, no doubt from shelling of the
Stalin's Organ.
19435.name: {MV{mector {MC{mity {MR{moad{x

description: The store is strewn with many common objects of different makes.  The
storekeeper is conversing with a townsman here, talking about the weather
and crops.  The storekeeper returns behind his counter as you enter.
19454.name: The Lucullus General Store

description: This road leads off of the road behind you which connects the
Magitek Stronghold to the Tower Structure.  The road leads off through

description: The Centre of the law and order for the small village is simple at best.
An old framed map and an obsolete gas lamp are objects that are attention
getting, and the desc is strewn with papers.
19467.name: Sherrif's Office

description: Shields, Armors, Helms, Swords, and other equipment of combat line the
walls of this shop.  The air is warm from the fire of the forge, as you see
the smith here hammering away at a new bladed creation.  The man sees you
enter, and wipes his forehead, as he leaves his anvil to help you in your
selection.
19456.name: Cargan's Implements of Destruction

description: The road leads through a field with burnt patchs all through it.
To the east you can see some old massive structures from previous
Vectorian projects.  To the southeast is the Magitek Stronghold, and
to the west and southwest is the Tower Structure.  The road continues

19529.name: {MR{moad {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MM{magiTek {MF{mactory{x

description: This room is stacked with wall to wall shelves with papers.  Files and
names of all the citizens and generations, deeds, and estates.  Everything
is in neat order, from A to Z.
19468.name: Filing Chambers

description: The road leads directly to the entrance of the Magitek Factory.  To
the east is another road going to older project buildings in the back
lots of the Vectorian Compound.  Back south is the Magitek Stronghold
and Tower Structure.
19531.name: {MR{moad {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MM{magiTek {MF{mactory{x

description: The road forks at your feet, demanding you to make a decision for
your destination.  Shall you journey to Vector, St.  Plattsburg?  Or
shall you go back home?  There is a sign with distances planted in the
ground here.
19428.name: {MT{mhe {MV{mectorian {MI{mntersection{x

description: A massive structure rises above you.  One of the four towers that
is suspending the massive building in the center.  The tower goes up
about four stories, and a building sits on top of it.  About 2 stories
up you can see a catwalk going along the side of the building.  To the
east is the Magitek Stronghold and Factory.

description: Northward bound holds the intersection, deciding the destination from
Vector or St.  Plattsburg.  During the night, the lights of Vector throw

wastes linger lightly.
19427.name: The Road To Vector

description: You see a stream ahead, with a plain wooden bridge to travel over.  The
stream flows swiftly despite its small size, and the peaceful, calming sound
it makes, paired with the chirping of birds in the nearby forest, makes for
a nice promenade.
19408.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: The peasants of the village seem to live a rather busy lifestyle despite
the small community itself.  There is laughter and song coming from the
east, where the tavern and inn dubbed {^The Laughing Lass{x is established,
and the West has A Temple devoted to Chauntea.
19416.name: Town of Lucullus

description: A spactious and luxourious, this room has a two single beds adorned with
soft sheets and down pillows.  A long rectangular window takes up the most
of the right-hand wall, showing the feilds and forest.
19461.name: A Double Room

description: The smells of home cooked food fills the room, and a series of appetizing
dishes have been served to the already eating patrons.  The waitress of the
day smiles and greets you as she passes by with her serving tray
19457.name: The Laughing Lass Diner

description: As you continue along the road, you can see that the foliage is gradually
clearing as a few rays of sunshine work hard to peirce their warmpth passed
the canopy.  The road will soon leave the forest, and you will be back in
open road soon.
19409.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: Leaving the Coastline, the road banks sharply.  You see tracks of recent
caravans having travelled the road.  The road itself is well used and
defined, but has many holes.
19442.name: The Road To St.Plattsburg

description: Nothing but the blowing wind and the reed-like rattleing of the grass are
audible.  The dusty road leaves a brown film on your shoes as you travel.
The dust disturbed by your feet is quickly carried into the crosswind,
leaving no trace of footsteps.
19421.name: The Road To Vector

description: As the road begins to pin into the Mirkwood, you begin to hear the sounds
of nature fill your ears.  But the sounds are like most other forests, they
are stranger...  More alien than most other forest they are stranger...
More alien than most other forest creatures, you can hear them shuffle
across the forest floor.  It's almost like you are being watched....
19403.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: The Mayor's office, being spacious and luxourios compared to the
secratary's workspace, has a large desk, and multiple windows.  A small
crystal ceiling-light illuminates the room, and a fireplace is agaist the
wall.  There are multiple paintings on the walls, and two tapestries, one of
the Tripower flag, and one of the Vectorian Flag, hang on the wall
19471.name: Mayor's Office

19484.name: {MM{main {MS{mtreet {MV{mector{x

19532.name: {MR{moad {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MM{magiTek {MF{mactory{x

description: A massive structure of steel rises above you in this spot.  One of
the Tower Structures that holds the massive building up.  The tower
stands about four stories high, with a building on the top.  You can
see leading off down the side and in front of the building a catwalk.
The dirt road continues to the west.
19490.name: {MU{mnder {MT{mhe {MW{mest {MA{mirship {MT{mower{x

description: The path, although well worn, is still rather forboding.  It almost
feels like the forest has eyes, and they watch you every move.  The various
birds here don't chirp happily, more like they seem to be communicating...
19405.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: The final mile to St.  Plattsburg is well maintained, with straight,
smooth roads, and clean ditches.  The city itself has an appealing view to
it, being foreshadowed by the sea.  The sounds of civilization are ambient,
yet apparant, as the hustle and bustle of life proceeds unhindered in St.
Plattsburg.
19449.name: The Road To St.Plattsburg

description: The dirt road leads along the western part of the Great Wall.  Back
south is the main doors, and the roads leading to the Magitek Factory
and the Magitek Stronghold.  This road leads to where the Vectorian
Prison was in the old fortress.
19488.name: {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MW{mest {MA{mirship {MT{mower{x

description: You stand at the end of Main Street Vector.  Before you is large
stone stairs leading up to the Fortress of Vector.  Two large doors
stand leading into the fortress.  The walls of the Fortress stand on
either side.  Back south is Main Street, the Magitek Factory and the
barren yard.
19485.name: {MT{mhe {ME{mnd {MO{mf {MM{main {MS{mtreet {MV{mector{x

description: You step into the dark forest.  All around you, you hear nothing
but the animals within, and other strange noises.  The forest is dark,
and cold, the road continues north.
19475.name: The Industrial Road

description: This end of town is ripe with activity.  There seem to be a few merchant
caravans stopping here to trade with the local blacksmiths and weapon
makers.  The modest shop to the west has it's doors opened to all those who
would enter.  Further northwest, you can see what seems to be the division
of the lands, marked by the patrol units of the Realms of Vector.
19418.name: Town of Lucullus

description: The dirt road leads away from the Tower Structures, the Magitek
Factory and the Stronghold, to where the prison once was when the
Fortress of Vector was here.  The road continues heading towards the
west.
19520.name: {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MP{mrison {MG{mates{x

description: The heavily travelled road to vector lies beaten down and almost torn
from the surrounding countryside.  Small hints of litter mark carelessness
of the travellers going to and from the capitol.
19430.name: {MV{mector {MC{mity {MR{moad{x

description: The path, although well worn, is still rather forboding.  It almost feels
like the forest has eyes, and they watch you every move.  The various birds
here don't chirp happily, more like they seem to be communicating...
19406.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: The eastern catwalk runs along the western side of the massive
building.  You see large port hatches lined up with gates along the
side of the catwalk.
19504.name: {ME{mastern {MC{matwalk{x

description: Finely finished Hardwood flooring and paintings adorn the halls which
lead to the rooms available for rent.
19458.name: Second floor of the Inn

description: The dirt road leads away from the Tower Structures, the Magitek
Factory and the Stronghold, to where the prison once was when the
Fortress of Vector was here.  The road continues heading towards the
west.
19521.name: {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MP{mrison {MG{mates{x

description: You stand in front of the doors leading into the fortress.  They
stand about two stories tall and is made from large beams.  They raise
up into the air into an archway.  The stonework on the archway follows
the door frame all the way down to the ground.  A large four story
wall extends in either direction.  Behind you is Main Street Vector
and the Magitek Factory.
19486.name: {MB{mefore {MT{mhe {MF{mortress {MO{mf {MV{mector{x

description: {BThe deep blue waters of the Istar Sea slowly slap against
{Bthe western shores, along the Plains of Torregiano.  To the
{Beast on the southern shore is the city of Torregiano.  The
{Bwestern shore passes by the township of Lucullus, known
{Bfor its world famous beer, and The Great Gorge.  And then
{Bthe shoreline goes into the Vectorian Empire shores.
19804.name: {BT{bhe {CI{Bs{bt{Ba{Cr {bSe{Ba{x [{GWestern Shore{x]

description: A new road leads off from the worn, old roads of Vector.  This road
goes north into the woods and into the unknown.  The road looks new,
and you see that a path has been cut through the forest ahead.
19472.name: The Industrial Road

description: Leaving the Coastline, the road banks sharply.  You see tracks of recent
caravans having travelled the road.  The road itself is well used and
defined, but has many holes.
19443.name: The Road To St.Plattsburg

description: With a Double King sized bed and silken sheets, fine wooden furniture,
and a pleasantly soft rug.  This room is one fit for a Monarch or more.
Everything in this room screames expensive, from the draperies, to the
paintings.  Everything is of extra fine quality, and there's even a balcony
with a view of the ocean!
19463.name: A suite fit for an Emperor

description: Northward bound holds the intersection, deciding the destination from
Vector or St.  Plattsburg.  During the night, the lights of Vector throw
beams into the night skies, and during the day, the smell of industrial
wastes linger lightly.
19426.name: The Road To Vector

description: The road, dusty and dry, gives small clouds of dirt to the air as you
pass along.  The scenery is repetitive and bland, forest to one side, and
grass and ocean to the next.  Though, in the far east distance, there are
structures marking the evidence of civilization.  St.  Plattsburg is to the
east across the bay.
19425.name: The Road To Vector

description: {BThe waves of the Istar Sea slowly flow over each other,
{Bsmall almost ripples.  The deep blue waters of the sea
{Bprotect what lies beneath, the darkness hiding unknown
{Bcreatures.  The water is almost surrounding, only the creset
{Bof a coastline appears on the hoizon.
19790.name: {BT{bhe {CI{Bs{bt{Ba{Cr {bSe{Ba{x

description: Before you stands the Gates of Vector.  A large wall extends in
either direction, higher than anything on the other side of the gates.
The gates stand tall.  Made from wrought iron.  Above the gates reads
Vector in the stone work of the archway above.  Inside you can see a
single street heading north through the city.  To the northeast you
can see another large facility.
19480.name: {MO{mutside {MT{mhe {MF{mortress {MO{mf {MV{mector{x

description: This is what could be called the governing power of this hamlet, being
the place where all relevant documents are kept.  Also the largest house in
the town, it probably previously was owned by a rich townsman.
19455.name: The Town Hall

description: {bThe waves of the Istar Sea slowly flow over each other,
{bsmall almost ripples.  The deep blue waters of the sea
{bprotect what lies beneath, the darkness hiding unknown
{bcreatures.  The water is almost surrounding, only the creset
{bof a coastline appears on the hoizon.
19788.name: {BT{bhe {CI{Bs{bt{Ba{Cr {bSe{Ba{x

description: Redwood and oak seem to mold this fine establishment, and the slight odor
of spices float in the air.  A large redwood counter borders off a part of
the lobby and conjoins with the staircase to the rooms.  A young man seems
to be attending at the counter, and ready to attend to your services.
19452.name: The Laughing Lass Inn

description: The walls of St.  Plattsburs are massive constructs of brown granite
rock.  No doubt the people inside have reason to feel secure with such
things surrounding them.  The view from the gate shows a busy city with
crowded streets.
19450.name: Before St.Plattsburg

description: Finely varnished hardwood floors hold your dull reflection as you walk
along the hall.  Local paintings adorn the walls, and a small mat to hold a
small table with a vase.
19460.name: Second floor of the Inn

description: The eastern catwalk runs along the western side of the massive
building.  You see large port hatches lined up with gates along the
side of the catwalk.
19503.name: {ME{mastern {MC{matwalk{x

description: The southern catwalk runs along in front of the massive building.
To the north you can see a large structure coming off of the building,
filled with alot of windows.  The catwalk runs east to west.
19500.name: {MS{mouthern {MC{matwalk{x

description: This was once the inside of the Fortress of Vector.  The great
outter wall of the building stands behind you.  The rest of the
building is gone, and something new has been built.  The foundation of
the Fortress can be seen, a large rock hole.  Above the foundation is
a massive building, suspended in the air by four towers, two on either
end of it.  Other parts of the old Fortress still excist.  To the
northeast you can see the MagiTek Factory.  To the east you can see
the MagiTek Stronghold.  To the west is a field and a forest.  To the
north a pair of large doors lead into the Geomancer.
19487.name: Before The Airship Fortress

description: A signpost piked into the ground points the directions and distances to
different possibile locations.  The closest one indicates the town,
{^Lucullus{x which you are in the presence of.  The small town is fenced
only by sporadic haystacks and livestock fences, yet has a feeling of
pleasant cozyness around it.  Children laugh and play in the nearby feilds,
obilivious to the world.  To the west, a quaint stable has taken its stake
on the land.
19415.name: Town of Lucullus

description: As you continue along the road, you can see that the foliage is gradually
clearing as a few rays of sunshine work hard to peirce their warmpth passed
the canopy.  The road will soon leave the forest, and you will be back in
open road soon.
19407.name: {MThe V{mectorian Ro{Madway{x

description: {BThe deep blue waters of the Istar Sea slowly slap against
{Bthe western shores, along the Plains of Torregiano.  To the
{Beast on the southern shore is the city of Torregiano.  The
{Bwestern shore passes by the township of Lucullus, known
{Bfor its world famous beer, and The Great Gorge.  And then
{Bthe shoreline goes into the Vectorian Empire shores.
19778.name: {BT{bhe {CI{Bs{bt{Ba{Cr {bSe{Ba{x [{GWestern Shore{x]

description: A spactious and luxourious, this room has a two single beds adorned with
soft sheets and down pillows.  A long rectangular window takes up the most
of the right-hand wall, showing the feilds and forest.
19464.name: A Double room

description: You stand on level two of the Tower Structure.  All around is you
metal girders and wires running down the towers to unknown sources.  A
ladder goes up through four floors of the tower, and into a control
room in the building at the top A large catwalk extends in either way,
to the east and to the north.  To the north you can see hatches on the
side of the building.  To the west passes in front of a large
operating room with large windows.  The ladder continues up and down.
The Control Building is directly above.
19496.name: {MW{mest {MA{mirship {MT{mower{*: {ML{mevel {R3{x

description: The road leads through a field with burnt patchs all through it.
To the east you can see some old massive structures from previous
Vectorian projects.  To the southeast is the Magitek Stronghold, and
to the west and southwest is the Tower Structure.  The road continues
its way to the Magitek Factory.
19438.name: {MR{moad {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MM{magiTek {MF{mactory{x

description: The road leads through a field with burnt patchs all through it.
To the east you can see some old massive structures from previous
Vectorian projects.  To the southeast is the Magitek Stronghold, and
to the west and southwest is the Tower Structure.  The road continues
its way to the Magitek Factory.
19528.name: {MR{moad {MT{mo {MT{mhe {MM{magiTek {MF{mactory{x

description: Nothing but the blowing wind and the reed-like rattleing of the grass are
audible.  The dusty road leaves a brown film on your shoes as you travel.
The dust disturbed by your feet is quickly carried into the crosswind,
leaving no trace of footsteps.
19420.name: The Road To Vector

description: A small shrine devoted to the Agriculture goddess Chauntea.  This is
where the citizens go to pray for a plentiful harvest in the coming
harvests.  Candles placed about the chamber give the shrine a soft warm
glow.  There is no sound in the room save your disturbances.
19453.name: Temple of Chauntea

description: The smell of animal droppings fill your senses as you walk in the animal
stable.  A quaint stable at best, but does hold promising looking purchases.
The owner of the stable is here tending to the daily needs of the stable
itself.  There is little variety of animals here, but adequate for most
standards.
19451.name: The Stables of Lucullus.

description: The final point before the Checkpoint to Vector holds an ominous
ambience.  Armed border patrols mark recent conflict, betrayal, and hate.
Cautious Guards throw a careful sneer at your approach, they seem to murmmer
between each other about somthing.  A few steps north will lead you out of
the Tri Power Lands and into uncertainty.
19422.name: The Road To Vector

description: The room is cramped with furniture and file cabinets.  The room is
spotted with stacks of papers, probably in the means of trade and exchange.
There is a oaken desk which a secratary is working at, and the east has the
door to the mayor's office.
19470.name: Mayor's Secratary's Office

description: You stand on level two of the Tower Structure.  All around is you
metal girders and wires running down the towers to unknown sources.  A
ladder goes up through four floors of the tower, and into a control
room in the building at the top A large catwalk extends in either way,
to the west and to the south.  To the north you can see hatches on the
side of the building.  To the west passes in front of a large
operating room with large windows.  The ladder continues up and down.
The Control Building is directly above.
19506.name: {ME{mast {MA{mirship {MT{mower{x: {RNORTHEAST{x

description: The northern catwalk runs along the rear of the massive building.
From here you can see two large metal fans, massive fan blades bigger
than a titan, and exhaust ports.  The catwalk runs east to west.
19507.name: {MN{morthern {MC{matwalk{x

description: You go deeper down the road, towards whatever is in that forest.
The war covered countryside surrounds you, there are even small
crators still smoking in the fields.  You see no one around.
19473.name: The Industrial Road

description: Deeper into the dark forest you go.  The animals around you, stop
for a moment to make sure you are not dangerous, and the forest seems
to go quiet.  Then as quickly as the silence comes, the noise starts
back up again.  With each step, the animals do this little game...
19476.name: The Industrial Road

description: You stand on level two of the Tower Structure.  All around is you
metal girders and wires running down the towers to unknown sources.  A
ladder goes up through four floors of the tower, and into a control
room in the building at the top.
19492.name: {ME{mast {MA{mirship {MT{mower{*: {ML{mevel {R2{x

description: The final stretch to Vector is a marked by distant checkpoints to screen
all those who would enter the capitol city.  The recent conflicts have made
the area a victim, and residual Makou-burn has trashed the surrounding
feilds and has scroched the ground.
19434.name: {MV{mector {MC{mity {MR{moad{x

{bcreatures.  The water is almost surrounding, only the creset
{bof a coastline appears on the hoizon.
